Bruegel: Peasant Wedding, Vienna, Wedding Dance, Detroit. Gilbert HIGHET, 'Bruegel's Rustic Wedding', Magazine of Art, XXXVIII, Nov. 1945, pp. 274-76 (with new and not convincing identification of bridegroom seated at end table on right, [onleesbaar] bride. His parents next to bride, supposed to be town people) see also Albert E. Elsen, Purposes of Art, 2nd ed. NY 1967, pp. 188 f.); Look up exh. Catal. (by C. Gilbert) Figures at a Table, John & Mabel Ringling Museum of Art, Saratoga, Flo., 1960; E. SCHEYER, 'The Wedding Dance in the Detroit Institute of Arts', Art Quarterly, XXXVIII, 1965, 167-93; W. GIBSON, 'Some Notes on Peter Bruegel the Elder's Peasant Wedding Feast', Art Quarterly, XXXVIII, 1965, 194-208.
